    </teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Leviticus 2</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Lev002-P159r-L5_trl" n="5"
                            prev="ADub.III.73.003.001.trl.xml#Lev001-P159r-L5_trl" />
                        <l n="1">And if a person
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             brings a grain offering to the Lord, his offering shall be of fine
                            flour.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             And he shall pour oil on it and put frankincense on it.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                        <l n="2">And he shall bring it to Aaron’s sons,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             the priests. And he shall take from there the fill of his fist from its
                            fine flour
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             and from its oil with all the frankincense, and the priest shall burn
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             its incense on the altar, an offering by fire, an aroma of acceptance
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             to the Lord.</l>
                        <l n="3">And the remnant of the grain offering shall be
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             for Aaron and his sons, the holy of holies from the Lord’s
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             offerings by fire.</l>
                        <l n="4">And if you bring an offering of a grain offering
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             baked in the oven, <supplied reason="lost">it shall be</supplied>
                            unleavened cakes of fine flour mixed with oil
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             or unleavened flans smeared with oil.</l>
                        <l n="5">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             if your offering is a grain offering made on a griddle,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             it shall be of fine flour mixed with oil, unleavened.</l>
                        <l n="6"><seg type="commented" corresp="#Lev-002-seg001_trl" />Break it into
                                pieces<anchor type="commented" xml:id="Lev-002-seg001_trl" /><ref
                                n="1" target="#Lev-002-fn1_trl" type="noteAnchor" />,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             and pour oil on it. It is a grain offering.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                        <l n="7">And if your offering is a grain offering baked in a pan,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             it shall be made of fine flour with oil.</l>
                        <l n="8">And you shall bring the
                            <milestone unit="page" n="159v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             grain offering that is made of these things to the Lord, and it shall
                            be brought
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             to the priest, and the priest shall bring it to the altar.</l>
                        <l n="9">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             And the priest shall separate from the grain offering its incense, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             he shall burn it on the altar, an offering by fire, an aroma of
                            acceptance to the Lord.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                        <l n="10">And that which is left of the grain offering shall be Aaron’s and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             his sons’: the holy of holies of the offerings by fire of the Lord.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                        <l n="11">Every grain offering that you bring to the Lord shall not be made
                            leavened,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             because you shall burn no leaven or any honey as an offering by fire to
                            the Lord.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                        <l n="12">The offering of a first thing: you shall bring them to the Lord,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             but they shall not go up to the altar for an aroma of acceptance.</l>
                        <l n="13">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             you shall salt every offering of your grain offering with salt, and you
                            shall not let the salt of the covenant of your God cease
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             from on your grain offering; you shall bring salt
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             on all your offerings.</l>
                        <l n="14">And if you offer
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             a grain offering of firstfruits to the Lord, you shall bring forward
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             a grain offering of your firstfruits: ears |of grain| parched in fire,
                                <supplied reason="lost">†torn</supplied><ref n="2"
                                target="#Lev-002-fn2_trl" type="noteAnchor" /> groats.</l>
                        <l n="15">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             And you shall put oil on it and lay
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             frankincense on it. It is a grain offering.</l>
                        <l n="16">And the priest shall burn
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             its incense, some of the groats, and some of the oil with all the
                            frankincense,
                            <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Lev002-P159v-L19_trl" n="19"
                                next="ADub.III.73.003.003.trl.xml#Lev003-P159v-L19_trl" />
                             an offering by fire to the Lord. </l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app>
                        <note xml:id="Lev-002-fn1_trl" type="footnote">Lit. ‘to divide it |into|
                            pieces’, a calque of BHeb. <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">פָּתֹות אֹתָהּ פִּתִּים </foreign>
                             ‘Break it into pieces’. The same Karaim construction is used in H, and
                            in C.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Lev-002-fn2_trl" type="footnote">An uncertain interpretation
                            of <emph>jyrtqan</emph>.</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
